snippet: Libya’s factions have agreed to a new round of negotiations backed by the United Nations to try to end the conflict that is destabilizing the country after its civil war in 2011.
abstract: United Nations says rival factions in Libya have agreed to new round of peace talks.
lead_paragraph: Libya’s factions have agreed to a new round of negotiations backed by the United Nations to try to end the conflict that is destabilizing the country after its civil war in 2011.

headline.main: Libya: Rival Factions Agree to Negotiations, U.N. Says
